TextChange: Trump defended far-right groups after a mass rally by white supremacists resulted in one young woman's death, and scores of others injuries, including, predominately people of color.  Trump claimed afterward that \"There were good people on both sides\".  This bland remark emboldened far right domestic terrorists.  The events of January 6, 2021 were the direct result.
At present, Americans are divided on this issue, as is Congress.  The very freedoms we enjoy are under threat as a result.
